1
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:39,167
<i>I don't know how I can
make you feel better.</i>

2
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:41,133
<i> But we'll help you.</i>

3
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:45,467
<i>Hazel, honestly, I want justice
for what happened to Jessica.</i>

4
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,267
<i>I don't know what
to think anymore.</i>

5
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:48,400
<i> Think of Jessica.</i>

6
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:50,967
<i> The justice she needs.</i>

7
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,233
<i> Think about that.</i>

8
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:53,400
<i> Seriously, Jeffrey?</i>

9
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:55,133
<i> Why did you go to Hazel again?</i>

10
00:00:55,267 --> 00:00:57,533
<i> Dad wanted to talk to Hazel.</i>

11
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:59,100
<i> So you met with Hazel.</i>

12
00:00:59,233 --> 00:01:01,433
<i>But what if the driver
truly believes</i>

13
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:03,167
<i> that Coleen pushed Jessica?</i>

14
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:06,133
<i> You've changed your mind</i>

15
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:08,300
<i>right after you met
with that Hazel woman!</i>

16
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:10,033
<i> Is Coleen Ruiz Cruz here?</i>

17
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:12,333
<i>We're here to arrest
your daughter.</i>

18
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,100
Mom?

19
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,100
Are you Coleen Cruz?

20
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,067
- Wait.
- Hold on, hold on!

21
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,067
Why would you handcuff her
right away?

22
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,967
Sweetie.

23
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:26,967
<i> Wait, wait.</i>

24
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,567
Wait, let's talk this out.

25
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:29,467
<i> Hold on, Sir.</i>

26
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,400
<i> Sir.</i>

27
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:34,200
Ma'am, the court has already
issued an order.

28
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:36,133
We're here to take your daughter
into custody.

29
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:37,667
We're just doing our job.

30
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,367
But my daughter is innocent!

31
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,067
It's for the court to decide.

32
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:43,500
God, please help us.

33
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:45,333
Coleen Cruz, we're arresting you

34
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,633
for killing
Jessica Capistrano Cruz.

35
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:48,767
I didn't kill her.

36
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,900
Wait. Sir, perhaps we could
discuss this first?

37
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,133
- My sister is innocent.
- Yeah.

38
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:53,600
Why would you handcuff
her right away?

39
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:55,867
And my sister's getting hurt,
Sir.

40
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,233
Wait, wait!

41
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:00,467
You have the right
to remain silent.

42
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:02,500
Anything you say can
and will be used against you

43
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:03,400
in a court of law.

44
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:05,667
You have the right
to an attorney.

45
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,367
If you cannot afford
an attorney,

46
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,400
one will be provided for you.

47
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:14,333
Do you understand the rights
that we've explained to you?

48
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,300
No.

49
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:19,100
Mom, Dad, please help me.

50
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:19,967
Don't be scared.

51
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:20,933
I'll go with you.

52
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:22,200
I'll go with you, Felma.

53
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:23,367
No, Manuel.

54
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,967
Call Atty. Yeban.

55
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:27,367
Please follow us to the precinct
right away, all right?

56
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,633
- Jeffrey, come with me.
- Let's go.

57
00:02:29,767 --> 00:02:30,400
- Mom.
- Andrea,

58
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:31,633
take care of everything here.

59
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:32,667
Paz, Abel.

60
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:36,200
- Don't pull her!
- Wait!

61
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,200
Be careful!

62
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:38,200
Hey!

63
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,200
Cheers to Coleen's arrest.

64
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:56,400
What did Attorney Salazar say?

65
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,167
Obviously, the driver's
statement helped the prosecutor

66
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:03,667
to decide to file the case.

67
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,167
So, is Coleen going
straight to jail?

68
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,600
Of course!

69
00:03:07,733 --> 00:03:11,800
Finally, Jessica's death
will be given justice.

70
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:13,900
Cheers!

71
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:15,400
All right!

72
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,833
Get her inside.

73
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:58,733
<i> Full name, Coleen Ruiz Cruz.</i>

74
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:00,500
How old are you?

75
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:01,267
Twenty years old, Sir.

76
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:08,000
That's her! That's her!

77
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:10,233
That's her! She pushed Jessica!

78
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:11,667
Listen to me!

79
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,633
- Malabanan!
- That's her!

80
00:04:12,767 --> 00:04:13,433
Stop it!

81
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:15,967
He's the driver
who hit Jessica.

82
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:19,367
If you hadn't pushed that woman,
I never would've run her over.

83
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,533
I wouldn't have gone to jail!

84
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:21,433
This is your fault!

85
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:22,533
I didn't push her!

86
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:23,500
It was your fault!

87
00:04:23,633 --> 00:04:24,867
- It was you!
- I didn't push her!

88
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,267
- It was you!
- No!

89
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:27,100
<i> It was you!</i>

90
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:29,267
Sir, please, believe me.

91
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:31,333
I couldn't do that.

92
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:32,300
She is my sister.

93
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,467
- Dear.
- I didn't push her, Sir.

94
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,933
Don't talk yet.

95
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,867
Atty. Yeban isn't here yet.

96
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,333
Call Atty. Yeban.

97
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:41,333
I didn't push her, Mom.

98
00:04:41,467 --> 00:04:42,333
He's texted me, Mom.
He's on his way here.

99
00:04:42,467 --> 00:04:43,500
The lawyer is on his way,
Coleen.

100
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,733
We can get through this.

101
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:48,000
That's enough.

102
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:50,167
Hush now. Stop crying, dear.

103
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:52,600
I couldn't do that.

104
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:54,700
She is my sister, Mom.

105
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,933
Felma's not replying
to my text messages.

106
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:23,400
What could've happened to them?

107
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:27,400
Bro, calm down.

108
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,867
Your lawyer is there already,
right?

109
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,333
He'll fix everything.

110
00:06:31,467 --> 00:06:33,533
What else can be done, Uncle?

111
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:37,033
Could they withdraw the case
against Coleen?

112
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:38,900
Is there anything they can do?

113
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:43,867
Your sister is too young
to be in this mess.

114
00:06:56,733 --> 00:06:57,567
Joel, sorry.

115
00:06:57,700 --> 00:06:59,200
Your party has been ruined.

116
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:00,133
I'm okay.

117
00:07:00,267 --> 00:07:01,533
Don't worry about me.

118
00:07:01,667 --> 00:07:03,367
We should prioritize Coleen.

119
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,700
<i> This is too hard for me.</i>

120
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,400
If only I had the strength
to walk,

121
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:09,633
I'd have gone with Felma
and comforted Coleen.

122
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:21,800
Cheers!

123
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:32,233
Congratulations, Attorney,
for a job well done.

124
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:33,200
Who would've thought?

125
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:35,133
The timing is perfect.

126
00:07:35,267 --> 00:07:38,867
Coleen is about to learn
the full heat of prison life.

127
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,400
She's going to be like
a sizzling<i> Sisig</i> .

128
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:43,800
Thank you, Mrs. Cruz.

129
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,367
What else do you want?

130
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,933
What food would you like me
to order?

131
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:49,867
Anything else?

132
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:50,600
Is there something
you still want?

133
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:52,400
Tell me, Attorney.

134
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:53,400
You deserve it.

135
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,567
Come on, tell me.

136
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:56,333
What else do you want?

137
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:58,700
This is enough.

138
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:02,933
<i>Mrs. Cruz, it's not that
I want to rain on your parade.</i>

139
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,833
But...

140
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:08,333
our fight has just started.

141
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:12,067
But you'll do everything

142
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,500
to keep Coleen from getting out
of prison, right?

143
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:18,067
It's still up to the court

144
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,867
how they will accept
Timo's testimony.

145
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,167
<i> I don't know.</i>

146
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:25,933
Something feels off.

147
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,233
Oh, please, Attorney.

148
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,267
Timo Malabanan is none
of your concern.

149
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,033
It's okay.

150
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:36,467
Just focus on winning the case.

151
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:44,933
And make sure that that woman
won't get out of jail anymore.

152
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:49,100
Relax.

153
00:08:49,233 --> 00:08:50,467
Go on and eat more, Attorney.

154
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:57,133
I thought you'd lost
your appetite.

155
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:59,400
Go on. You so deserve it.

156
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:10,833
Mom.

157
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:11,967
Mom.

158
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,800
Mom, I don't want it here.

159
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:16,400
Please bring me back home.

160
00:09:16,533 --> 00:09:18,200
Please, Mom.

161
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,367
Dear, dear.

162
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,600
There's nothing we can do.

163
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:22,767
We have to follow the law.

164
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:23,567
Okay?

165
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,867
Sir, I didn't do anything wrong.

166
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,733
I didn't push my sister.

167
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,700
Please believe me.

168
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,400
I would never do that to her.

169
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:35,167
Miss Cruz, you need
to get inside now.

170
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,400
Let's go.

171
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:39,067
- Mom.
- Go on, sweetheart.

172
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,567
- Do as they say.
- Mom.

173
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,367
<i>She has to go inside, Miss Ruiz.</i>

174
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:42,933
Go on.

175
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:43,867
Mom!

176
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,000
Mom!

177
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:50,733
Come on, let's go.

178
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:54,433
Mom!

179
00:09:54,567 --> 00:09:56,100
- Mom!
- Go inside.

180
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,000
Come on.

181
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:02,067
Mom!

182
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:06,067
Mom!

183
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:11,300
Mom!

184
00:10:14,667 --> 00:10:15,867
Mom.

185
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:20,433
Sweetie, we'll find a way
to get you out of here.

186
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:21,167
Okay?

187
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,000
I want to go home, Mom.

188
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:25,300
I want to go home.

189
00:10:28,533 --> 00:10:33,167
Attorney, is my daughter's case
bailable?

190
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:37,267
If it can be proven
in the bail hearing

191
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:39,300
that the evidence of guilt
is weak,

192
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:42,267
then yes, Ma'am,
we can post bail for her.

193
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,967
But that won't happen
immediately,

194
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,800
because we still need to file it
in court.

195
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:50,533
And the office is closed
tomorrow

196
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:52,300
because it's the weekend.

197
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:53,267
What does it mean?

198
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,733
Coleen will stay here
for a few days?

199
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,767
Sorry, that's how it works.

200
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:04,533
Mom.

201
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:10,867
We're here for you.
You're not alone.

202
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:14,200
I don't want it here.

203
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:16,800
I don't want to.

204
00:11:29,167 --> 00:11:30,967
It won't be until Monday
that the attorney can file

205
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:31,933
for bail.

206
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,667
Coleen is going to stay in jail
for a few more days.

207
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,633
Oh, no.

208
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,967
My poor baby.

209
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,133
She's not used to the heat.

210
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:49,767
Mom, is there nothing else
we can do?

211
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:52,500
Let's do something
to get her out today.

212
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,500
We can't do anything.

213
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,700
But how is she?

214
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,767
She's crying non-stop.

215
00:12:01,567 --> 00:12:02,900
She wants to go home.

216
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:33,567
Here.

217
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,000
Lay that on the floor
so you don't get cold.

218
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:40,567
Just get it.
No need for all that fuss.

219
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:57,133
Thank you, Miss.

220
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:58,467
Just call me Emmy.

221
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,900
Miss is so formal.

222
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:05,433
How old are you?

223
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:07,833
I'm twenty.

224
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:08,933
My God, you're so young.

225
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:11,233
<i> What brought you here?</i>

226
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:13,600
You killed your sister,
didn't you?

227
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:16,200
I didn't kill her.

228
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:18,100
That's what everyone says.

229
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:20,533
That's not true!

230
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:22,033
I didn't kill my sister.

231
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,133
They're accusing me of
something I didn't do.

232
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:28,733
The driver, Timo Malabanan,
is the one who killed my sister.

233
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,200
Do you even know
what I'm guilty of?

234
00:13:33,667 --> 00:13:36,433
That I didn't make peace
with my sister sooner.

235
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:40,733
I allowed things
between us to blow up.

236
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:45,133
And when I finally wanted
to apologize, it was too late.

237
00:13:45,267 --> 00:13:47,100
And the most painful part?

238
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:49,100
She died still angry at me.

239
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:55,100
I will never get the chance
to know if she forgave me.

240
00:13:56,533 --> 00:14:00,567
I will never get the chance
to make things right.

241
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:02,433
Do you know how painful that is?

242
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:04,967
Do you?

243
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,267
Ma'am Felma.

244
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:37,067
This is Coleen's favorite.

245
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:43,500
What if she gets sentenced?

246
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:49,200
What if she ends up
locked up for good?

247
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,667
Will she even get
to wear this again?

248
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:57,267
Ma'am Felma, you're thinking way
too far ahead.

249
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:01,233
If only you saw Coleen
inside that cell...

250
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,267
She was terrified, Dad.

251
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,867
You know that feeling?

252
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,133
Like, suddenly your whole world
changes?

253
00:15:08,133 --> 00:15:09,900
And she's surrounded by people
she's never even met.

254
00:15:11,367 --> 00:15:16,100
While we're here, happy,
together,

255
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:18,133
and living more comfortably.

256
00:15:18,267 --> 00:15:24,200
I've done nothing
but serve my children.

257
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:34,500
I worked myself to the bone just
to give them a good future...

258
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,133
a good life.

259
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,333
So they'd never have
to struggle...

260
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:44,133
or be pushed to do
something wrong.

261
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,833
Like what happened to Jeffrey.

262
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,433
I don't want any of my children
ending up in jail.

263
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:59,700
And now,
Coleen might end up there.

264
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,567
I'm supposed to be
the black sheep of this family.

265
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:06,600
I'm always the failure,
the disappointment.

266
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:08,200
It should be me in there,
not Coleen.

267
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:11,733
Jeff, please don't say that.

268
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:15,333
None of my children
deserves to be jailed.

269
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,800
You're all good kids.

270
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:21,000
You don't deserve to go
through anything like that.

271
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:27,933
Ma'am Felma,
let's trust in the Lord.

272
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:33,033
I know the truth will come out.

273
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:36,233
Coleen will be acquitted.

274
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,067
I hope so, Didang.

275
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:45,767
I really hope we can trust
the court to uphold justice.

276
00:16:49,667 --> 00:16:52,167
And I hope people won't be
swayed so easily.

277
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:59,500
They want to destroy
Coleen and our family.

278
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:04,267
If I could do anything
to help your sister.

279
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,733
If I could trade places
with her,

280
00:17:05,867 --> 00:17:08,400
if I could be the one jailed
instead, I would.

281
00:17:08,533 --> 00:17:10,767
You know what, Dad?
I'd do the same.

282
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:14,433
Yes, son. But we can't let
ourselves drown in sadness.

283
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:17,467
We have to stay strong
for Coleen.

284
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,300
Didang, thank you.

285
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:21,500
Thank you.

286
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:23,533
I finally let out all the fear.

287
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:29,467
Now I can be strong again
for my children.

288
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,667
Yes, Ma'am.

289
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:32,767
Thank you.

290
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:35,733
<i> Mom?</i>

291
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:39,733
Mom, what's wrong?

292
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,400
I'm fine.

293
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:47,067
But it's okay to cry, Mom.

294
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:50,367
I understand you.

295
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:54,333
What our family is going
through is really tough.

296
00:17:57,533 --> 00:17:58,900
But don't worry, Mom.

297
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:01,300
We're here.

298
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:04,067
As long as we stay together...

299
00:18:06,267 --> 00:18:07,567
we'll stay strong.

300
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,333
For each other.

301
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:13,467
For Coleen.

302
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:20,033
You, your mother, Andrea,
and I will work together.

303
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:22,300
We have to stay strong

304
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:26,533
so Coleen can feel
she has people to lean on.

305
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:28,100
<i> So she can hold on</i>

306
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:31,067
<i>and believe we'll get through
this trial together.</i>

307
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:44,433
Special wine for this
special celebration.

308
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:50,767
Yes, of course.

309
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:53,733
Yes!

310
00:18:53,867 --> 00:18:55,000
This one tastes better.

311
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:57,267
Hey!

312
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,900
Wow.

313
00:18:59,033 --> 00:19:00,700
Delicious!

314
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:04,400
But this one is even better.

315
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,700
Oh my God.

316
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:08,533
Definitely way better
than the last one.

317
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:09,533
Yes!

318
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:10,833
Yes!

319
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,600
Delicious!

320
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:13,500
Cheers!

321
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:15,333
Thank you for inviting us!

322
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:19,133
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

323
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,167
Wow!

324
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,633
Unbelievable!

325
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:38,833
Friend, congratulations.

326
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:40,867
You are definitely having fun.

327
00:19:42,233 --> 00:19:45,333
Of course, I am.

328
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:47,533
I am so happy right now.

329
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:50,067
I mean, Coleen is in jail.

330
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:56,700
I'm sure Felma's whole family
is in chaos.

331
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:04,100
Maybe she and Manuel are blaming
each other right now.

332
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:05,000
Right?

333
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:10,267
At least somehow, I've finally
gotten back at them

334
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,733
for what happened to Jessica.

335
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:14,767
Poor thing.

336
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:23,567
I love you, friend!

337
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:24,867
I love you too, friend.

338
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:48,167
Sir, we just want to bring
some food for our daughter.

339
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,933
Ma'am, I'm really sorry.

340
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:53,567
But visiting hours
are already over.

341
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:57,467
Sir, we won't take long.

342
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,333
Please, can't you allow
it just this once?

343
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:03,500
We're begging you, Sir.

344
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,000
We brought a lot of food.

345
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:08,600
Good for sharing.

346
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,800
It's not just for our daughter.

347
00:21:13,367 --> 00:21:15,067
Please, Sir...

348
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,500
We're asking for your kindness.

349
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:18,467
<i> Mom?</i>

350
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:20,567
Dad?

351
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:24,300
Mom?

352
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:27,000
Dad?

353
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,800
- Sir, please.
- Sir.

354
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:32,300
- Please let us see her.
- Mom!

355
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,900
Mom...

356
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:20,333
Dad...

357
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:27,167
Dear, we brought you your
favorite food and your things.

358
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:34,633
Is there really no chance
for me to get out of here?

359
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:43,333
Mom, this is the first time I've
ever been separated from you.

360
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,167
I know.

361
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,900
And it hurts me just as much,
sweetheart.

362
00:23:04,867 --> 00:23:11,300
If I could, I would stay
in that cell with you.

363
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:15,167
Just so we don't have
to be apart.

364
00:23:16,867 --> 00:23:20,933
I will speak with the officers
if you like, dear.

365
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:23,300
Maybe they'll allow me
to stay here with you,

366
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:25,833
just until we post bail.

367
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:29,133
Dad, come on.

368
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:32,467
You and mom are making me cry.

369
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:35,500
We're only thinking about
what's best for you.

370
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:41,600
Dear, we know how hard
it is for you in here.

371
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,233
It's hot.

372
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:48,500
Our sleeping area
isn't even decent.

373
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:55,367
But that's not the reason
I want to go home.

374
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:02,067
I don't know the people
I'm with.

375
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:05,267
I'm not sure
if I can trust them.

376
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:10,700
Even with them around,
I still feel completely alone.

377
00:24:12,633 --> 00:24:15,767
It's different when
I'm at home with you.

378
00:24:17,367 --> 00:24:22,600
Dad, Mom, I don't want
to be away from you anymore.

379
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:38,733
Do you know what the penalty
for your case is?

380
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:41,267
Reclusion perpetua.

381
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:43,500
Lifetime imprisonment.

382
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:45,733
Did you really have
to argue on camera?

383
00:24:45,867 --> 00:24:49,367
This kind of exposure
doesn't help.

384
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:50,500
Felma is already stressing
me out,

385
00:24:50,633 --> 00:24:51,633
and now you're adding to it.

386
00:24:51,767 --> 00:24:54,033
Timo is much easier to handle,
you know.

387
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:55,533
Timo?

388
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:58,733
Mom, is what Hazel said true?

389
00:24:58,867 --> 00:25:01,367
That I'll never get out of here?

390
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,200
She said I'd be transferred
to the city jail

391
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:07,700
and I'd stay there forever.

392
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:10,167
Boss, you need to see this.

393
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:11,167
When did this happen?

394
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:12,500
- Where?
- At the precinct

395
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:14,467
where Miss Felma's daughter
is detained.

396
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,500
Cancel my flight.

397
00:25:16,633 --> 00:25:18,867
And call Atty. Vital.

398
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,167
Tell him to meet me ASAP.
